OL,6,FThe Ingram-Moores have argued it was a
OL,7,F"breach of privacy" for the book deal
OL,8,Fto have been disclosed by the Charity
OL,9,FCommission and said "significant fees"
OL,10,Fhad been paid to the literary agent,
OL,11,Flegal and PR professionals, as well as
OL,12,Fsome money having "supported" the
OL,13,Ffoundation.
OL,15,FThe commission's report found a
OL,16,F"repeated pattern of behaviour" which
OL,17,Fsaw the couple make private gains and
OL,18,Fwhich the watchdog said will have left
OL,19,Fthe public feeling "misled".
